ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Visit name
Scale rating participant initial pain level before the test, as part of the 10 Meter Walk Test
Scale rating participant pain level after the test, as part of the 10 Meter Walk Test
Time in seconds (with one decimal) duration to complete the 10 Meter Walk Test
Indicator of completion of the 10 Meter Walk Test
Reason for 10 Meter Walk Test not being completed
Notes: 1 = Did not attempt; 2 = Initiated but unable to complete; 3 = Other

ElementDescription: Indicator of assistance used during the 10 Meter Walk Test
Cane used for assistance, as part of the 10 Meter Walk Test
Crutches (1 or 2, any gait pattern) used for assistance, as part of the 10 Meter Walk Test
Walker used for assistance, as part of the 10 Meter Walk Test
Personal assistance or support used for assistance, as part of the 10 Meter Walk Test
Other assistance used, as part of the 10 Meter Walk Test
Other assistance used, as part of the 10 Meter Walk Test (specify)
Free-text comments in the 10 Meter Walk Test
Blood pressure screening, within study range indicator; as part of the Five Times Sit to Stand (5TSTS) Test
Notes: 1 = Within study range (90/60 to 160/90 mmHg); 2 = Out of study range (less than 90/60 OR greater than 160/90 mmHg)

ElementDescription: Scale rating initial level of pain, as part of the Five Times Sit to Stand (5TSTS)
Scale rating final level of pain, as part of the Five Times Sit to Stand (5TSTS)
Time in seconds (with one decimal) duration to complete test as part of the Five Times Sit to Stand (5TSTS)
Indicator of completion of the Five Times Sit to Stand (5TSTS)
Reason for non-completion of the Five Times Sit to Stand (5TSTS)
Notes: 0 = Did not attempt: Participant declined or deemed unsafe; 1 = Initiated, but subject unable to complete; 2 = Other

ElementDescription: Number of reps completed as part of the Five Times Sit to Stand (5TSTS)
Indicator of any assistance used as part of the Five Times Sit to Stand (5TSTS)
Indicator of assistance in the form of push-off from the arms of the chair or use of an assistive device as part of the Five Times Sit to Stand (5TSTS)
Indicator of assistance in the form of personal assistance (any type of hands-on assistance or support during task, even if only briefly or for balance)as part of the Five Times Sit to Stand (5TSTS)
Free-text of additional notes as part of the Five Times Sit to Stand (5TSTS)
